body:
IMHO build time network access is generally a bad idea.

And actually CDPx pipeline (the build system used in msazure) doesn't even allow network access except for nuget restore and publishing build artifacts.
You can preinstall MKL, and avoiding use MKLML.

But how to use MKL?
I thought there's only MKLML code path in CMake files.

> Hi @jywu-msft,
> What do you think?

it should be possible to link against the full MKL (but what is the use case? if you just want to use gemm, I think MKLML is sufficient)

to link against full MKL, I think we need to use the MKLDNN_USE_MKL option and set it to either ML (for MKLML) or FULL to link against full MKL. and would also need to set MKLROOT environment variable to path where MKL is installed.

see: https://github.com/intel/mkl-dnn/blob/master/cmake/options.cmake#L66

here's the logic https://github.com/intel/mkl-dnn/blob/master/cmake/MKL.cmake#L91
it's using to find full MKL or MKLML

@jywu-msft 
There're 2 use cases:
  1. When user already have full MKL as part of its dependency
  2. Avoid re-download MKLML every time.

I know how to let MKLDNN uses full MKL.
I'm talking about the case when `-Donnxruntime_USE_MKLML=ON -Donnxruntime_USE_MKLDNN=OFF`.

@xkszltl 
Do you have a specific use case for using full MKL vs MKLML ? 
MKLML is already stripped down version of MKL yet is still quite large at 150MB.  
onnxruntime currently can only take advantage of cblas_sgemm from MKLML/MKL 
In the longer term, MKLDNN's gemm should reach performance parity with MKL cblas_sgemm 
Unless we have specific use of other functionality in MKL/MKLML, it seems better to use MKLDNN
(btw, the DNN functionality in the full MKL package is being deprecated. it is advised to use MKLDNN for DNN features)

Re: avoiding re-download MKLML,  maybe you can leverage intel's script for downloading MKLML instead 
see: https://github.com/intel/caffe/blob/master/external/mkl/prepare_mkl.sh

Correct me if I'm wrong but I think the download is triggered by https://github.com/Microsoft/onnxruntime/blob/a3499083dae79c5737c2d31d9512068f89cb48e1/cmake/external/mkldnn.cmake#L40
And there's no way around it without code modification.
yes, there needs to be code modification.
It'll be great if there's a similar mechanism like MKLDNN_USE_MKL for onnxruntime.
FYI here's also a scenario where mkl can be useful: #530
